WEBVTT

00:00.900 --> 00:03.100
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:03.100 --> 00:06.000
♪ BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:06.000 --> 00:10.367
♪ WANDERIN' DOWN THIS ROAD
THAT WE CALL LIFE ♪

00:10.367 --> 00:12.700
♪ IS WHAT WE'RE DOIN' ♪

00:12.700 --> 00:14.500
♪ IT'S GOOD TO KNOW
I HAVE FRIENDS ♪

00:14.500 --> 00:16.300
♪ WHO WILL ALWAYS ♪

00:16.300 --> 00:18.767
♪ STAND BY ME ♪

00:18.767 --> 00:21.300
♪ WHEN THIS BOY MEETS WORLD ♪

00:26.233 --> 00:29.667
TOPANGA, HOW COULD YOU BE
SO CALM ABOUT THIS?

00:29.667 --> 00:31.700
BECAUSE I'M ONE
OF 500 QUARTERFINALISTS,

00:31.700 --> 00:33.400
AND I'M NOT GONNA GET IT.

00:33.400 --> 00:36.767
UNH-UNH. CORY,
TELL HER HOW HUGE THIS IS.

00:36.767 --> 00:39.734
YOUNGEST DEAD GUY
YESTERDAY -- 42.

00:39.734 --> 00:42.233
UGH!

00:42.233 --> 00:46.567
WOW! A SUMMER INTERNSHIP
WITH BROWN-ELLIOT!

00:46.567 --> 00:48.600
BROWN-ELLIOT?

00:48.600 --> 00:52.100
WOW, THAT'S THE MOST PRESTIGIOUS
LAW FIRM IN NEW YORK.

00:52.100 --> 00:54.467
THEY REPRESENT
MY<i>RICH </i>STEPFATHER.

00:54.467 --> 00:56.200
CONGRATULATIONS.

00:56.200 --> 00:57.900
THANK YOU.

00:57.900 --> 00:59.600
OH, NO, NO, NO --

00:59.600 --> 01:02.500
I WAS CONGRATULATING MYSELF
ON MY<i>RICH </i>STEPFATHER...

01:02.500 --> 01:04.000
WHO, BY THE WAY,

01:04.000 --> 01:07.467
IS BANKROLLING
MY NEW BUSINESS VENTURE --

01:07.467 --> 01:09.000
i'mjack.com.

01:09.000 --> 01:12.100
SO, WHAT EXACTLY IS THE CONCEPT
OF THIS<i>BUSINESS?</i>

01:12.100 --> 01:15.767
I'M JACK.

01:15.767 --> 01:17.834
I DON'T GET IT.

01:17.834 --> 01:20.600
DOT COM?

01:20.600 --> 01:23.100
OH.

01:23.100 --> 01:25.100
I'M GRADUATIN'!
I'M SMART!

01:28.000 --> 01:32.033
HEY, YOU WANT TO KNOW
HOW THIS POOR SCHMO DIED?

01:32.033 --> 01:34.000
A BIRD FLEW IN HIS MOUTH.

01:34.000 --> 01:37.400
A<i>PIGEON-- </i>
NOT EVEN A CLASSY BIRD!

01:37.400 --> 01:39.000
SO, UH,
I JUST GOT A QUESTION --

01:39.000 --> 01:41.400
ARE YOU SUPPOSED TO WEAR PANTS
WITH THESE THINGS?

01:41.400 --> 01:43.200
OH, MY GOSH!
OH!
OH!

01:45.000 --> 01:47.600
PUT YOUR DRESS DOWN,
MATTHEWS.

01:47.600 --> 01:49.600
ALL RIGHT.

01:49.600 --> 01:51.900
DADDY!

01:51.900 --> 01:53.500
HOW'S MY BABY GIRL?

01:53.500 --> 01:54.834
ALL RIGHT.

01:54.834 --> 01:56.200
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?!

01:56.200 --> 01:57.900
WELL, I DIDN'T COME
TO SEE<i>THAT.</i>

02:02.200 --> 02:03.867
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

02:03.867 --> 02:06.900
YEAH, EVERYTHING'S FINE.
I'VE BEEN REASSIGNED, ANGELA.

02:06.900 --> 02:07.967
NEAR HERE?

02:07.967 --> 02:09.800
NO, TO EUROPE.

02:09.800 --> 02:13.200
THAT'S NOT NEAR HERE.
NO, I'M SORRY, HONEY.

02:13.200 --> 02:15.200
I THOUGHT YOU REQUESTED
TO BE CLOSER TO ME.

02:15.200 --> 02:18.700
I DID, BUT MY ORDERS
ARE TO UPGRADE SECURITY

02:18.700 --> 02:20.600
AT THE EMBASSIES.

02:20.600 --> 02:22.700
BY THE WAY,
THAT'S HIGHLY CLASSIFIED.

02:22.700 --> 02:25.100
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:25.100 --> 02:27.300
UHH.

02:27.300 --> 02:29.133
HMM.

02:29.133 --> 02:31.834
SO, DADDY, HOW LONG
IS IT GONNA BE THIS TIME?

02:31.834 --> 02:33.967
A YEAR.
A YEAR?

02:33.967 --> 02:36.000
THAT'S FOREVER!

02:36.000 --> 02:37.934
NOT IF YOU COME WITH ME.

02:39.734 --> 02:41.467
WHAT?

02:41.467 --> 02:44.767
I WANT YOU TO COME WITH ME
TO EUROPE, ANGELA.

02:46.400 --> 02:47.900
HEH-HEH-HEY!

02:47.900 --> 02:51.200
THERE'S THE MAN WHO PUT ME
AND ANGELA BACK TOGETHER!

02:51.200 --> 02:52.567
SHAWN.

02:52.567 --> 02:54.200
HOW ARE YA?

02:54.200 --> 02:55.934
Sgt. Moore: GOOD.

03:01.367 --> 03:02.900
BEEN TAKING CARE
OF YOUR DAUGHTER.

03:02.900 --> 03:04.600
I KNEW YOU WOULD.

03:04.600 --> 03:06.100
HI, BABY.

03:06.100 --> 03:07.600
HI.

03:07.600 --> 03:09.200
WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

03:09.200 --> 03:11.233
HI.

03:11.233 --> 03:13.000
I'M SURE YOU TWO
HAVE A LOT TO TALK ABOUT.

03:13.000 --> 03:14.567
I'LL BE BACK AT THE HOTEL.

03:14.567 --> 03:16.500
WE SHOULD HAVE DINNER
LATER, SIR.

03:16.500 --> 03:18.367
YEAH, I'D LIKE THAT.

03:18.367 --> 03:20.600
GOOD.

03:20.600 --> 03:22.900
OKAY, WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

03:22.900 --> 03:24.767
OKAY, WHAT'S GOIN' ON?!

03:24.767 --> 03:27.500
WELL, I'M UP FOR THIS
BROWN-ELLIOT INTERNSHIP --

03:27.500 --> 03:30.133
YOU, YOU, YOU, YOU!
I'M TALKIN' ABOUT SHAWN!

03:30.133 --> 03:33.500
OH, ANGELA'S DAD INVITED HER
TO GO TO EUROPE WITH HIM.

03:33.500 --> 03:35.467
SHAWN HAS NO IDEA.

03:35.467 --> 03:37.000
COME ON,
HOW BAD CAN IT BE

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
WITH ALL THE STUFF
THAT GOES ON IN MY LIFE?

03:39.000 --> 03:40.500
[ SIGHS ]

03:40.500 --> 03:42.567
MY FATHER WANTS ME
TO GO WITH HIM TO EUROPE.

03:42.567 --> 03:44.100
THAT'S IT?

03:44.100 --> 03:46.000
YEAH, BUT --

03:46.000 --> 03:48.500
GO TO EUROPE WITH YOUR FATHER!
WHERE'S BAD THERE?

03:48.500 --> 03:50.400
FOR A<i>YEAR.</i>

03:50.400 --> 03:52.900
<i>THERE'S </i>BAD.

03:57.200 --> 04:00.200
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

04:00.200 --> 04:01.567
WOW, EUROPE.
NO.

04:01.567 --> 04:03.400
I CAN JUST
SEE HER NOW --

04:03.400 --> 04:05.133
SITTING
IN AN OUTDOOR CAFE,

04:05.133 --> 04:07.200
READING POETRY,
SIPPING ESPRESSO.

04:07.200 --> 04:08.967
YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
THEY GOT

04:08.967 --> 04:10.834
BESIDES CAFES IN EUROPE,
SHAWN?

04:10.834 --> 04:13.500
THEY GOT<i>MEN...</i>

04:13.500 --> 04:16.200
MEN NAMED "PAOLO"...

04:16.200 --> 04:19.467
"ENRIQUE"...

04:19.467 --> 04:20.900
"MILOS"...

04:20.900 --> 04:23.200
AND THEY SIT THERE,

04:23.200 --> 04:25.800
PROWLING AROUND
IN THEIR DIRTY FERRARIS

04:25.800 --> 04:28.300
LOOKING FOR THAT FRESH
AMERICAN MEAT!

04:28.300 --> 04:30.200
LOOK, I TRUST ANGELA.

04:30.200 --> 04:32.100
[ French accent ]
AH HA HA HA HA!

04:32.100 --> 04:34.934
MY LITTLE CROISSANT,
JUMP INTO MY PEUGEOT,

04:34.934 --> 04:37.867
AND WE WILL DRIVE
ON THE WRONG SIDE OF THE ROAD!

04:37.867 --> 04:40.200
[ Imitating Angela ]
BUT I LOVE SHAWN!

04:40.200 --> 04:42.967
[ French accent ]
PHOOEY ON SHAWN!

04:42.967 --> 04:45.400
IF I WAS YOUR MAN,
I WOULD NEVER LET YOU GO!

04:45.400 --> 04:47.500
SHAWN CANNOT POSSIBLY
SATISFY YOU!

04:47.500 --> 04:50.500
HE'S A LITTLE TRAILER BOY
WITH A STUPID AMERICAN --

04:50.500 --> 04:52.500
OKAY, OKAY, SHUT UP!

04:52.500 --> 04:55.667
[ Normal voice ] I LOVE THAT YOU
CAN JUST LIE TO YOURSELF,

04:55.667 --> 04:57.667
WHILE YOUR LIFE
IS JUST FALLIN' APART.

04:57.667 --> 04:59.700
REALLY!
I JUST FIND IT ADORABLE.

04:59.700 --> 05:01.567
I WANT ANGELA TO BE HAPPY.

05:01.567 --> 05:04.500
YOU'RE A LIAR! A YEAR AWAY
WILL KILL YOUR RELATIONSHIP!

05:04.500 --> 05:06.734
HOW OFTEN DO YOU GET
TO SPEND TIME WITH YOUR FATHER?

05:06.734 --> 05:08.700
THAT'S NICE, SHAWN.

05:08.700 --> 05:12.367
ARE YOU GONNA "NICE" YOURSELF
OUT OF THE GIRL YOU LOVE?

05:12.367 --> 05:15.300
NO.

05:15.300 --> 05:17.667
I'VE LOST TOO MANY PEOPLE
THAT LOVE ME.

05:17.667 --> 05:19.367
I'M NOT LETTIN' THIS ONE GO.

05:19.367 --> 05:21.300
GOOD.

05:21.300 --> 05:23.867
I'M GONNA TELL HER TO STAY.

05:23.867 --> 05:25.600
<i>NICHT! </i>
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

05:25.600 --> 05:26.900
WHY NOT?

05:26.900 --> 05:29.000
YOU CAN'T MAKE THIS DECISION
FOR HER.

05:29.000 --> 05:31.734
THAT WOULD BE LIKE ME TELLIN'
TOPANGA SHE CAN'T GO TO YALE.

05:31.734 --> 05:34.000
IT'S A DECISION
SHE'S GOTTA MAKE ON HER OWN.

05:34.000 --> 05:35.400
ISN'T THAT RISKY?

05:35.400 --> 05:37.033
YOU SAID SHE LOVES YOU.

05:37.033 --> 05:38.767
SHE DOES.

05:38.767 --> 05:40.233
THEN THERE'S NO RISK.

05:40.233 --> 05:42.300
LISTEN TO ME --
TAKE IT FROM EXPERIENCE.

05:42.300 --> 05:44.700
WOMEN HAVE GOT TO GO
THROUGH A PROCESS.

05:44.700 --> 05:47.033
WITH WOMEN, IT'S ALL
ABOUT THE<i>PROCESS...</i>

05:47.033 --> 05:49.467
AND SHOES.

05:49.467 --> 05:51.667
SO IF I LET HER
GO THROUGH THIS PROCESS,

05:51.667 --> 05:54.233
SHE'LL MAKE THE DECISION TO STAY
ALL BY HERSELF?

05:54.233 --> 05:56.200
YES, AND SHE'LL LOVE YOU
EVEN MORE,

05:56.200 --> 05:58.200
AND SHE'LL STAY RIGHT HERE,
NEVER GO ANYWHERE,

05:58.200 --> 06:00.200
AND ALWAYS BE
IN THAT LIVING ROOM.

06:00.200 --> 06:02.600
HUH. THIS WILL BE, LIKE,
THE FIRST TIME

06:02.600 --> 06:04.700
THAT EVERYTHING'S
TURNED OUT OKAY IN MY LIFE.

06:04.700 --> 06:06.100
DEFINITELY.

06:06.100 --> 06:08.800
THE ONLY MONKEY WRENCH
IS THAT I'VE NOTICED

06:08.800 --> 06:11.667
MOST OF TOPANGA'S SHOES...
COME FROM EUROPE.

06:14.500 --> 06:17.367
BUT, DAD!
BUT, DADDY!

06:25.900 --> 06:28.400
THE PEACE CORPS COULD BE
A GREAT WAY TO SEE THE WORLD

06:28.400 --> 06:30.367
AND HELP PEOPLE
AT THE SAME TIME.

06:30.367 --> 06:31.567
YEAH, YEAH, PEACE.

06:31.567 --> 06:33.934
I REALLY NEED TO TALK
ABOUT<i>ME </i>RIGHT NOW.

06:33.934 --> 06:36.033
I HAVE A SERIOUS CRISIS
ON MY HANDS HERE.

06:36.033 --> 06:37.934
YEAH, YOU -- CRISIS.

06:37.934 --> 06:40.400
WHAT COULD GO WRONG IN THAT
STUPID, CHARMED LIFE OF YOURS?

06:40.400 --> 06:42.300
I'M POOR.

06:46.100 --> 06:48.033
MY STEPDAD'S CUTTING ME OFF,
RACHEL.

06:48.033 --> 06:50.200
WHY?

06:50.200 --> 06:52.300
HE DOESN'T WANT ME
TO START i'mjack.com.

06:52.300 --> 06:54.600
HE THINKS IT'S RISKY.
I THINK IT'S BRILLIANT.

06:54.600 --> 06:57.033
IDIOT! HE WANTS ME
TO BE AN INVESTMENT BANKER

06:57.033 --> 06:59.133
AND TO FOLLOW
IN HIS FOOTSTEPS.

06:59.133 --> 07:01.233
WELL, THEN WORK
FOR YOUR DAD.

07:01.233 --> 07:02.967
I WANT TO START
MY<i>OWN </i>BUSINESS.

07:02.967 --> 07:05.600
THEN START
YOUR OWN BUSINESS.

07:05.600 --> 07:07.500
HOW? I'VE GOT NO MONEY!

07:07.500 --> 07:10.133
I CAN'T BE POOR!
I'M TOO GOOD-LOOKING TO BE POOR!

07:10.133 --> 07:14.767
JACK, STICK TO YOUR PRINCIPLES,
BECAUSE WITHOUT PRINCIPLES,

07:14.767 --> 07:18.400
YOU'RE NOTHING
BUT A SHALLOW, SOULLESS SCUM.

07:18.400 --> 07:20.900
YES, HELLO,
JACK'S RICH STEPFATHER?

07:20.900 --> 07:22.767
I'LL BE YOUR SON FOR MONEY.

07:22.767 --> 07:25.300
WELL, IT SOUNDS PAINFUL, SIR,
BUT I'LL DO IT FOR MONEY.

07:26.600 --> 07:28.867
HEY, TOPANGA.
HI, CORY.

07:28.867 --> 07:30.734
LISTEN, I'M SO SORRY
FOR WHAT I DID.

07:30.734 --> 07:31.867
WHAT DID YOU DO?

07:31.867 --> 07:34.000
AREN'T WE FIGHTING?

07:34.000 --> 07:35.834
NO.

07:35.834 --> 07:39.100
YEAH, BUT I-I WOKE UP ALONE.
I THOUGHT WE HAD A SLEEP FIGHT.

07:39.100 --> 07:40.867
CORY, I HAD
MY ON-CAMPUS INTERVIEWS

07:40.867 --> 07:42.934
FOR THE BROWN-ELLIOT INTERNSHIP
THIS MORNING.

07:45.000 --> 07:48.233
OH, YEAH!
HEY, BROWN-ELLIOT!

07:48.233 --> 07:50.000
ALL RIGHT! HA HA.

07:50.000 --> 07:53.000
HOW'D THAT, UH,
HOW'D THAT WORK OUT FOR YA?

07:53.000 --> 07:54.233
I'M NOT SURE.

07:54.233 --> 07:56.500
I REALLY APPRECIATED IT
WHEN THEY ALL APPLAUDED FOR ME,

07:56.500 --> 07:58.967
BUT THOSE THINGS
CAN BE SO HARD TO READ.

07:58.967 --> 08:01.734
BUT THEY'VE NARROWED IT DOWN
TO ONLY 100 CANDIDATES.

08:01.734 --> 08:03.967
MM-HMM. THAT'S --
THAT'S GREAT.

08:03.967 --> 08:05.734
GOOD FOR YOU.
SHAWN!

08:05.734 --> 08:07.400
THANKS, HONEY.

08:07.400 --> 08:10.133
ALL RIGHT,
NOW AFTER ANGELA TELLS YOU

08:10.133 --> 08:13.233
THAT SHE'S DECIDED
TO STAY HERE,
WHAT DO<i>YOU </i>SAY?

08:13.233 --> 08:16.300
I WANTED HER TO STAY, AND LIFE
IS MISERABLE WITHOUT HER.

08:16.300 --> 08:18.100
AND THIS WILL?

08:18.100 --> 08:21.300
VALIDATE HER DECISION...
AND GIVE ME LOTS OF KISSES.

08:21.300 --> 08:22.900
I'VE TAUGHT YOU WELL.

08:22.900 --> 08:24.600
NOW GO GET YOUR GIRL,
YOU CRAZY KID!

08:27.700 --> 08:28.900
Okay.

08:28.900 --> 08:31.200
OH!

08:31.200 --> 08:32.767
HI.

08:32.767 --> 08:34.800
HEY.

08:34.800 --> 08:36.700
YOU KNOW I'M GOIN' CRAZY
ABOUT THIS.

08:36.700 --> 08:37.934
ME TOO.

08:37.934 --> 08:39.500
THANKS FOR LETTING<i>ME </i>
WORK IT OUT.

08:39.500 --> 08:41.700
NO, HEY, YOU HAD TO GO
THROUGH YOUR PROCESS.

08:41.700 --> 08:44.033
WELL, I WENT BACK AND FORTH
SO MANY TIMES,

08:44.033 --> 08:46.767
BECAUSE YOU MEAN EVERYTHING
IN THE WORLD TO ME.

08:46.767 --> 08:49.000
YOU MEAN EVERYTHING TO ME.

08:49.000 --> 08:51.500
AND I COULD NEVER
LEAVE YOU.

08:51.500 --> 08:54.900
AND I COULD NEVER
LEAVE YOU.

08:58.400 --> 09:03.100
UNLESS...YOU SAID
I COULD GO.

09:03.100 --> 09:04.667
WHAT?

09:04.667 --> 09:06.600
WHEN WILL I EVER GET
A CHANCE LIKE THIS

09:06.600 --> 09:08.934
TO BE WITH MY FATHER?

09:16.767 --> 09:18.600
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN
FOR TWO DAYS?

09:18.600 --> 09:20.400
SPENDIN' ALL MY TIME
WITH ANGELA.

09:20.400 --> 09:22.200
THAT'S WHAT I LIKE
TO HEAR.

09:22.200 --> 09:24.033
DID SHE TELL HER DAD
THE BAD NEWS?

09:24.033 --> 09:25.600
HOW'D HE TAKE IT?

09:25.600 --> 09:27.467
SHE'S GOIN' TO EUROPE, COR.

09:27.467 --> 09:28.467
SHE'S WHA--

09:28.467 --> 09:29.467
SHE'S LEAVING.

09:29.467 --> 09:32.100
WHOA.
REWIND FOR A SECOND.

09:32.100 --> 09:35.567
WELL, WE SAT DOWN, AND SHE SAID
THAT SHE WOULDN'T GO

09:35.567 --> 09:37.567
IF I TOLD HER NOT TO.

09:37.567 --> 09:39.400
BUT, YOU KNOW,
SHE WANTS TO GO.

09:39.400 --> 09:42.100
SHE WANTS TO BE WITH HER DAD.
WHAT COULD I DO?

09:42.100 --> 09:44.567
OHH!
ARE YOU NUTSY-FAKIN'?!

09:44.567 --> 09:47.900
SHE WANTS YOU
TO FIGHT FOR HER, MAN!

09:47.900 --> 09:49.800
NO, THERE'S NO FIGHT.
THE PROCESS -- IT'S OVER.

09:49.800 --> 09:51.100
SHE'S GOING.

09:51.100 --> 09:52.734
SHE'S TESTING YOU.

09:52.734 --> 09:54.600
SHE WANTS YOU TO SHOW HER
HOW MUCH YOU LOVE HER.

09:54.600 --> 09:55.900
SHE KNOWS.

09:55.900 --> 09:58.300
YEAH, BUT APPARENTLY NOT ENOUGH
TO KEEP HER FROM GOING.

09:58.300 --> 10:00.767
I MEAN,
YOU FAILED THE TEST, SHAWN.

10:00.767 --> 10:03.000
YOU FORGOT TO PAY ATTENTION
TO WHAT SHE WANTS.

10:03.000 --> 10:04.500
TOPANGA --

10:04.500 --> 10:06.834
TOPANGA IS ALWAYS
TESTING ME -- ALWAYS.

10:06.834 --> 10:08.867
IT'S NOTHIN' BUT TESTS
BETWEEN ME AND THE OLD LADY,

10:08.867 --> 10:10.500
BUT I ALWAYS PASS.

10:10.500 --> 10:12.700
YOU WANNA KNOW WHY, SHAWN?
BECAUSE I PAY ATTENTION!

10:12.700 --> 10:14.400
OKAY, WISH ME LUCK.
I'M LEAVING.

10:14.400 --> 10:16.033
GOOD LUCK.

10:16.033 --> 10:18.000
WHAT -- YOU'RE LEAVING
<i>YOUR </i>MAN, TOO, TOPANGA?

10:18.000 --> 10:20.300
NO, I HAVE THE FINAL ROUND
OF INTERVIEWS IN NEW YORK.

10:20.300 --> 10:22.000
I'LL BE BACK
BEFORE ANGELA LEAVES, THOUGH.

10:22.000 --> 10:24.133
HEY, ANGELA IS<i>NOT </i>
LEAVING, OKAY?

10:24.133 --> 10:26.100
THAT'S NEGATIVE,
AND WE DO NOT NEED

10:26.100 --> 10:28.300
ANY NEGATIVE NELLIES
AROUND RIGHT NOW,

10:28.300 --> 10:29.667
SO GOODBYE, "NELLIE."

10:29.667 --> 10:30.934
[ CHUCKLES ]

10:33.400 --> 10:35.033
CAN I HELP YOU?

10:35.033 --> 10:36.867
AREN'T YOU GONNA KISS ME
FOR GOOD LUCK?

10:36.867 --> 10:37.934
GOOD LUCK.

10:37.934 --> 10:39.233
THANKS.

10:39.233 --> 10:41.200
SHAWN, YOU FAILED.

10:41.200 --> 10:43.667
YOU FAILED BECAUSE YOU HAVE
ABSOLUTELY NO IDEA

10:43.667 --> 10:45.934
WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH YOUR WOMAN!

10:45.934 --> 10:47.300
WHERE WAS TOPANGA GOING?

10:47.300 --> 10:49.467
I DON'T KNOW.
LAUNDROMAT?

10:49.467 --> 10:53.600
OKAY, WHY WOULD ANGELA
SAY THAT SHE WANTS TO GO

10:53.600 --> 10:55.567
IF SHE DOESN'T?

10:55.567 --> 10:58.100
BECAUSE HOW CAN SHE TURN DOWN
HER OLD MAN

10:58.100 --> 11:00.133
UNLESS SOMEONE TELLS HER TO?

11:00.133 --> 11:02.600
HER FATHER'S A STRONG GUY,
SHAWN.

11:02.600 --> 11:04.834
OKAY? HE TOLD HER TO GO,
BUT SHE WAS WAITING

11:04.834 --> 11:08.000
FOR AN EVEN STRONGER PERSON
TO TELL HER<i>NOT </i>TO.

11:08.000 --> 11:10.967
[ SIGHS ]
YOU'RE RIGHT.

11:10.967 --> 11:12.700
I DIDN'T FIGHT.

11:12.700 --> 11:14.700
I LET -- I LET HER GO.

11:14.700 --> 11:16.500
YOU TOLD ME TO DO NOTHING!

11:16.500 --> 11:19.367
NO, I TOLD YOU TO DO NOTHING
IF SHE DECIDED TO<i>STAY.</i>

11:19.367 --> 11:22.133
IF SHE DECIDED TO<i>GO, </i>
WHAT IDIOT WOULDN'T DO
SOMETHING?

11:22.133 --> 11:24.467
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I HAVE TO TELL YOU THAT!

11:24.467 --> 11:26.033
OKAY, DON'T YELL AT ME.

11:26.033 --> 11:27.767
DID YOU ONCE ASK HER
TO STAY?

11:27.767 --> 11:28.834
NO.

11:28.834 --> 11:31.600
THEN WHAT CHOICE
DOES SHE HAVE BUT TO GO?

11:31.600 --> 11:34.300
NONE.

11:34.300 --> 11:37.567
IT'S YOU VERSUS HER DAD.

11:37.567 --> 11:40.700
I-I REALIZE
YOU LIKE THE GUY, SHAWN,

11:40.700 --> 11:43.867
BUT YOU'RE FIGHTING
FOR THE WOMAN YOU LOVE.

11:48.033 --> 11:50.033
ANGELA!

11:50.033 --> 11:53.033
ANGELA WENT TO GET MORE BOXES.
SHE'LL BE BACK SOON.

11:53.033 --> 11:55.600
UM, SHE'S NOT LEAVING, SIR.

11:55.600 --> 11:57.100
SHE'S NOT?

11:57.100 --> 11:59.600
NO, I'M GONNA ASK HER TO STAY,
AND SHE WILL,

11:59.600 --> 12:01.600
BECAUSE SHE WANTS TO BE
WITH ME.

12:01.600 --> 12:04.600
SHAWN, ANGELA'S LEAVING
WITH ME.

12:04.600 --> 12:06.734
HUH.

12:06.734 --> 12:09.734
I THOUGHT
YOU WERE MY FRIEND.

12:09.734 --> 12:11.300
WE<i>ARE </i>FRIENDS.

12:11.300 --> 12:12.767
YEAH?

12:12.767 --> 12:14.767
'CAUSE WHAT KIND OF FRIEND
PUTS US TOGETHER,

12:14.767 --> 12:16.600
AND THEN RIPS US APART

12:16.600 --> 12:18.967
BECAUSE HE WANTS TO GO
TO EUROPE?

12:18.967 --> 12:20.967
THAT WAS NEVER MY INTENTION,
SHAWN.

12:20.967 --> 12:22.400
OH, IT WASN'T?

12:22.400 --> 12:24.667
WELL, THEN, WHAT<i>WAS </i>YOUR
INTENTION?

12:24.667 --> 12:26.867
BECAUSE YOU'RE TAKIN' HER AWAY
FROM HER FRIENDS

12:26.867 --> 12:28.734
AND THE PERSON
WHO LOVES HER.

12:28.734 --> 12:31.800
SHE'S GOT A LIFE HERE.
HOW COULD YOU DO THAT TO HER?

12:31.800 --> 12:34.100
I WANT WHAT'S BEST
FOR ANGELA.

12:34.100 --> 12:36.233
<i>I'M </i>WHAT'S BEST
FOR ANGELA.

12:36.233 --> 12:38.734
I AM HERE FOR HER
EVERY SINGLE DAY OF HER LIFE.

12:38.734 --> 12:40.967
CAN<i>YOU </i>SAY THAT, SIR?

12:44.100 --> 12:46.600
NO, I CAN'T.

12:46.600 --> 12:48.500
WELL, I CAN.

12:48.500 --> 12:50.500
AND I KNOW WHAT THAT'S WORTH,

12:50.500 --> 12:52.734
BECAUSE NO ONE
THAT LOVED ME EVER WAS --

12:52.734 --> 12:55.700
NOT MY MOM, NOT MY DAD.

12:55.700 --> 12:57.867
LOOK, I'M SORRY
THAT HAPPENED TO YOU, SON.

13:00.400 --> 13:02.033
YOU KNOW,
I WENT AWAY ONCE.

13:02.033 --> 13:03.934
YEAH, ANGELA TOLD ME
ABOUT THAT.

13:03.934 --> 13:07.400
I LEFT EVERYONE BEHIND
THAT MEANT ANYTHING TO ME.

13:07.400 --> 13:09.867
AND THAT'S
WHAT BROUGHT ME BACK --

13:09.867 --> 13:12.700
WHEN I REALIZED
THAT<i>NOTHING </i>OUT THERE

13:12.700 --> 13:14.467
MEANT MORE THAN THE PEOPLE

13:14.467 --> 13:17.467
THAT ARE HERE FOR YOU
EVERY...SINGLE...DAY!

13:17.467 --> 13:19.900
LOOK, I KNOW
HOW YOU FEEL, SHAWN.

13:19.900 --> 13:23.033
I'VE SPENT FAR TOO MUCH TIME
AWAY FROM MY DAUGHTER.

13:23.033 --> 13:24.867
THIS MAY BE MY LAST CHANCE

13:24.867 --> 13:26.867
TO SPEND SOME REAL TIME
WITH HER.

13:26.867 --> 13:28.700
THIS MAY SOUND SELFISH,

13:28.700 --> 13:30.800
BUT I'M NOT GONNA LET ANYTHING
GET IN THE WAY OF THAT.

13:33.500 --> 13:35.600
WELL, THIS MAY SOUND SELFISH,
BUT...

13:35.600 --> 13:38.000
WHAT IF I ASKED HER
TO MARRY ME?

13:38.000 --> 13:41.233
UHH...

13:41.233 --> 13:42.867
YOU SAID YOU LIKED ME.

13:42.867 --> 13:45.734
HOW MUCH DO YOU LIKE ME NOW?

13:48.500 --> 13:50.233
[ LAUGHING ]

13:50.233 --> 13:51.700
[ LAUGHING ]

13:54.834 --> 13:57.000
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT WE'RE LAUGHING AT.

13:57.000 --> 13:59.000
I'M VERY UNCOMFORTABLE, SIR.

13:59.000 --> 14:03.133
IF YOU AND ANGELA DECIDE
THAT YOU WANT TO GET MARRIED --

14:03.133 --> 14:05.200
YOU THINK YOU CAN TAKE CARE
OF EACH OTHER

14:05.200 --> 14:07.100
FOR THE REST OF YOUR LIVES...

14:08.934 --> 14:11.467
...THEN I'LL STEP ASIDE,

14:11.467 --> 14:14.400
AND LET YOU BE THE MOST
IMPORTANT MAN IN HER LIFE.

14:16.834 --> 14:18.834
GUESS WE'RE JUST TWO GUYS
WHO LOVE THE SAME GIRL

14:18.834 --> 14:20.700
AND WANT WHAT'S BEST
FOR HER.

14:20.700 --> 14:24.667
WELL, THEN, ONE OF US
BETTER FIGURE OUT WHAT THAT IS.

14:24.667 --> 14:26.500
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:26.500 --> 14:28.834
WHAT'S GOIN' ON HERE?

14:28.834 --> 14:30.100
NOTHIN'.

14:30.100 --> 14:32.400
WE WEREN'T EVEN TALKIN'
ABOUT YOU.

14:32.400 --> 14:36.367
YOU CAME TO SAY GOODBYE
TO ME?

14:36.367 --> 14:37.700
NO.

14:37.700 --> 14:39.967
NO, I WILL NEVER
SAY GOODBYE TO YOU,

14:39.967 --> 14:42.834
BECAUSE IF I SAY GOODBYE TO YOU,
THAT'S IT -- THAT'S GOODBYE.

14:42.834 --> 14:45.033
YOU'RE RIGHT --
WE SHOULD NEVER SAY GOODBYE,

14:45.033 --> 14:47.467
BECAUSE WE'RE GONNA WRITE
EACH OTHER EVERY DAY,

14:47.467 --> 14:49.300
AND WE'RE GONNA CALL
EACH OTHER,

14:49.300 --> 14:51.700
AND IT WILL BE LIKE
WE'VE NEVER EVEN BEEN APART.

14:51.700 --> 14:56.767
YES, EXACTLY --
WE SHOULD NEVER BE APART.

14:56.767 --> 14:58.667
I LOVE YOU.

14:58.667 --> 15:00.600
I LOVE YOU, TOO.

15:00.600 --> 15:04.800
AND WHEN -- WHEN YOU LOVE
SOMEBODY, ANGELA,

15:04.800 --> 15:07.834
IT'S OKAY TO BE
A LITTLE SELFISH.

15:07.834 --> 15:09.100
YEAH?

15:11.600 --> 15:14.100
THANK YOU...
FOR LETTING ME BE SELFISH.

15:14.100 --> 15:15.500
NO.

15:15.500 --> 15:17.600
NO, NO, NO,
NOT YOU -- ME.

15:17.600 --> 15:21.100
LOOK, THERE'S SOMETHING
I GOTTA ASK YOU RIGHT NOW.

15:21.100 --> 15:24.300
YOU KNOW, BECAUSE YOU'RE
THE ONLY PERSON THAT KNOWS

15:24.300 --> 15:26.300
HOW IMPORTANT IT IS

15:26.300 --> 15:28.934
FOR ME AND MY DAD
TO SPEND THIS TIME TOGETHER.

15:32.000 --> 15:36.567
I ONLY WISH YOU AND YOUR DAD
HAD THIS TIME TOGETHER.

15:36.567 --> 15:38.567
I'M SO SORRY YOU DIDN'T.

15:40.600 --> 15:44.100
THANK YOU
FOR GIVING ME MY CHANCE.

15:50.400 --> 15:53.300
I'M REALLY HAPPY
FOR BOTH OF YOU.

15:57.834 --> 16:00.300
WHAT WAS IT
THAT YOU WANTED TO ASK ME?

16:02.667 --> 16:05.233
OH, NEVER MIND.

16:05.233 --> 16:08.033
I FIGURED IT OUT.

16:15.200 --> 16:17.967
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

16:17.967 --> 16:20.600
OH, OUR WORLD TRAVELER'S
HERE!

16:20.600 --> 16:22.200
ANGELA!
WHOO!

16:22.200 --> 16:23.500
GUYS --

16:23.500 --> 16:25.233
OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE LEAVING.

16:25.233 --> 16:27.300
MY ROOM IS GONNA BE SO BIG
WITHOUT MY ROOMIE.

16:27.300 --> 16:29.767
I'LL BE BACK SOONER
THAN YOU THINK.

16:29.767 --> 16:32.300
YEAH, BUT<i>I </i>WON'T BE HERE.
I'M GRADUATING.

16:32.300 --> 16:34.200
AW, RACHEL.

16:34.200 --> 16:36.734
ANGELA. OH!

16:36.734 --> 16:38.100
WOW.

16:38.100 --> 16:40.467
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE
A GREAT TIME IN EUROPE.

16:40.467 --> 16:42.200
I'M SURE OF IT.

16:42.200 --> 16:44.834
OH, I WISH YOU GUYS
WERE COMING WITH ME.

16:44.834 --> 16:47.100
YEAH, I WISH, TOO,
BUT IT'S FUNNY,

16:47.100 --> 16:49.600
'CAUSE I REALLY CAN'T AFFORD
TO GO ANYWHERE ANYMORE.

16:49.600 --> 16:51.567
[ Voice breaking ]
OH, JACK!

16:51.567 --> 16:52.834
Oh, Jack.

16:52.834 --> 16:54.400
ANGELA!

16:54.400 --> 16:55.600
ERIC!

16:55.600 --> 16:57.900
ANGELA! COME ON.
COME ON.

16:57.900 --> 17:00.200
LET IT OUT, GIRL.
LET IT OUT.

17:00.200 --> 17:02.100
OOH! MMM, LET IT OUT!

17:02.100 --> 17:04.467
ERIC, WE'RE<i>TOUCHING.</i>

17:04.467 --> 17:09.100
♪ OO-OOH, CHILD,
THINGS ARE GONNA GET EASIER ♪

17:09.100 --> 17:12.400
♪ OO-OOH, CHILD,
THINGS WILL GET BRIGHTER ♪

17:12.400 --> 17:14.300
COME ON, MOVE WITH ME.

17:14.300 --> 17:16.834
HOW AM I SUPPOSED
TO SURVIVE WITHOUT MONEY?

17:16.834 --> 17:19.567
OH, JACK, YOU'RE JUST GONNA
HAVE TO SCALE IT DOWN --

17:19.567 --> 17:22.200
NO MORE FANCY RESTAURANTS,
NO MORE DESIGNER CLOTHES,

17:22.200 --> 17:24.133
NO MORE $50 HAIRCUTS.

17:24.133 --> 17:26.000
BUT THAT'S<i>JACK! </i>

17:26.000 --> 17:28.500
I CAN'T DO THAT TO JACK!

17:28.500 --> 17:30.500
YOU'RE REALLY DESPERATE,
AREN'T YOU?

17:30.500 --> 17:32.000
IT'S KIND OF FUN.

17:32.000 --> 17:33.467
OH, JACK.

17:33.467 --> 17:35.400
I WANT YOU
TO DO ME A FAVOR --

17:35.400 --> 17:37.367
HAND THESE OUT TO ALL
THE EUROPEAN GIRLS YOU SEE.

17:37.367 --> 17:39.700
TELL THEM IF THEY WANT ME
TO BE THEIR AMERICAN BOYFRIEND,

17:39.700 --> 17:43.100
MY NUMBER'S RIGHT THERE
AT THE BOTTOM OF THE PICTURE.

17:43.100 --> 17:45.033
NOW, I'VE ONLY GOT 500,

17:45.033 --> 17:48.000
SO DON'T BE HANDIN' THEM OUT
TO ANY HAIRY CHICKS, ALL RIGHT?

17:48.000 --> 17:50.567
I'LL DO MY BEST.

17:50.567 --> 17:53.500
I'M GONNA MISS YOU.
YOU WERE ALWAYS MY FAVORITE.

17:53.500 --> 17:54.800
REALLY?

17:54.800 --> 17:56.467
I DON'T KNOW.

18:01.300 --> 18:03.400
CORY, IS SHE GONNA MAKE IT?

18:03.400 --> 18:05.300
YEAH, YEAH,
SHE'LL BE HERE.

18:05.300 --> 18:07.367
SHE'S BEEN BUSY LATELY
DOIN' --

18:07.367 --> 18:09.033
I DON'T KNOW -- SOMETHIN'.

18:09.033 --> 18:10.934
CORY?

18:10.934 --> 18:12.100
YEAH?

18:12.100 --> 18:13.467
THANKS.

18:13.467 --> 18:14.934
FOR WHAT?

18:14.934 --> 18:17.767
FOR BEING MY FRIEND --
BELIEVING IN ME AND SHAWN

18:17.767 --> 18:20.233
AS MUCH AS YOU BELIEVE
IN YOU AND TOPANGA.

18:20.233 --> 18:22.200
I OWE YOU.

18:22.200 --> 18:23.967
WHERE IS SHE?
WHERE IS SHE?

18:23.967 --> 18:26.100
TOPANGA!

18:26.100 --> 18:28.934
I WAS AFRAID
I WASN'T GONNA MAKE IT.

18:28.934 --> 18:31.200
I'M GONNA MISS YOU
SO MUCH.

18:31.200 --> 18:34.500
YEAH, BUT WHAT AM I GONNA DO
WITHOUT MY BEST FRIEND?

18:34.500 --> 18:36.500
YOU'RE GONNA DO GREAT.

18:36.500 --> 18:38.400
SEND ME SHOES.

18:42.500 --> 18:44.400
YOU READY, BABY?
THE CAB'S WAITING.

18:54.900 --> 18:56.767
LET'S NOT SAY "GOODBYE."

18:56.767 --> 18:59.867
LET'S JUST SAY,
"I LOVE YOU."

19:02.200 --> 19:05.000
I love you, too.

19:05.000 --> 19:07.500
I ALWAYS WILL.

19:16.200 --> 19:19.200
TAKE CARE OF HER, SIR.

19:19.200 --> 19:21.100
YOU'RE A GOOD MAN, SHAWN.

19:21.100 --> 19:23.600
THANK YOU FOR GIVIN' ME
AND MY DAUGHTER THIS CHANCE.

19:23.600 --> 19:26.467
WELL...

19:26.467 --> 19:28.867
I KNOW
HOW IMPORTANT IT IS.

19:38.133 --> 19:39.834
[ SIGHS ]

19:48.934 --> 19:50.900
GOODBYE, ANGELA.

19:58.567 --> 20:02.500
DON'T SPIN
OUT OF CONTROL, OKAY?

20:02.500 --> 20:04.300
CORY...

20:04.300 --> 20:07.233
I GOT
THAT BROWN-ELLIOT INTERNSHIP.

20:07.233 --> 20:08.934
HUH?

20:08.934 --> 20:11.834
THEY OFFERED ME A SCHOLARSHIP
AT N.Y.U. LAW SCHOOL.

20:11.834 --> 20:15.033
AND THEY TOLD ME THAT ONCE
I GRADUATE AND PASS THE BAR,

20:15.033 --> 20:17.800
THEY WOULD LIKE ME
TO WORK FOR THEIR FIRM.

20:17.800 --> 20:20.000
WHAT ARE --

20:20.000 --> 20:21.500
WHO --

20:21.500 --> 20:23.467
WHERE IS THIS COMING
FROM YOU?

20:23.467 --> 20:25.100
WHAT --

20:25.100 --> 20:27.200
WHAT ARE --
WHAT HAVE YOU BEEN DOING?

20:27.200 --> 20:30.700
CORY, WE HAVE TO MOVE
TO NEW YORK.

20:30.700 --> 20:33.600
DON'T SPIN OUT OF CONTROL.

20:33.600 --> 20:36.200
WE -- WHY -- WHY --
WHY DID --

20:36.200 --> 20:38.000
WHY DID NO ONE TELL ME?!

20:38.000 --> 20:40.233
WHY DID NO ONE TELL ME?!
SOMEONE'S GOTTA TELL ME!

20:40.233 --> 20:42.233
SOMEONE'S ALWAYS
GOTTA TELL CORY!

20:42.233 --> 20:45.467
WHY, GOD?!
WHY?! WHY?!
